verbose_text: Farnesol, a 15-carbon sesquiterpene (an isoprenoid intermediate of the mevalonate pathway), is produced in cells by the dephosphorylation of farnesyl pyrophosphate, a precursor of squalene generating-sterols and other isoprenoid compounds.
